<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
I tried out nightly as of 2004-7-16, and the 'wall destruction' thaumaturgic spell seems to be gone.  Was this intentional?  I didn't see a comment in the changes.txt file about it. <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: The thaumaturgic spells are randomly determined. Sometimes you obtain a wall destruction spell, sometimes you don't. Checked it with the latest 2.3.0 (CVS) version, and the wall destruction spell is still available. 
</p>
<p>
Have the probabilities changed?  I tried for much of the night and put max points into Thaumaturgy just to see if I could find the spell for about half a dozen characters (I got them each up into the 20s before quiting and trying again; up to "e" level Thaumaturgy spells).  Very odd. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Afaik thaumaturgy was not changed in the 2.3.0 version. It is easier to test this in wizard mode: Create a testing character, type CTRL + W (answer yes) to enter wizard mode, go to the skill menu (G) and press + at the Thaumaturgy skill, until it reaches 50. 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


